<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6363/1523: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-09">March 9,
                                    1944</date>.<lb/>[Received March 10—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>784. Moscow papers for March 9th publish a Tass despatch from London
                                concerning the forthcoming conversations between Britain and the
                                United States concerning oil and listing the American
                                representatives. The item includes statement at a press conference
                                that other United Nations may participate in the conference.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>